   discourages frequent changing of requirements, which is a significant
   problem to designers. Compared with SSAD, Component-Based Software
   Engineering (CBSE) with its modular structured solution allows
   individual components to be replaced easily at design time or run time
   if the requirements of the initial component (expressed via the
