   scale systems evolve during lengthy development periods due to changes
   in software and business environments, new user needs and technological
   advancements. Agile methods, which focus on accommodating change even
   late in the development lifecycle, can be adopted for the development of
   larger scale systems. However, as currently applied, these practices are
   not always suitable for the development of such systems. We propose a
   soft-structured framework combining the principles of agile and
