   instruments in terms of control, monitoring as well as data acquisition
   and storage The framework also contains operation control tools.
   The user interaction features include data search and retrieval, data
   distribution. Current developments in the Web 2.0 area will provide a
   complete research environment where users will have the ability to work
   and interact on-line with colleagues, process and visualize data,
   establish observation schedules and pre-program autonomous, event
   detection and reaction. We call this environment ``Oceans 2.0{''}.
   The architecture of DMAS is focused on limiting the amount of data loss
   and maximizing up time. It is a service oriented architecture, making
   use of some of the more advanced tools available. The code is written in
