   ERCIM; OptimaNumerics; INTEL; AMD},
Abstract = {The Rational Unified Process (RUP) is a development process which is
   based on object-oriented, usecase-centric, architecture-centric, and
   iterative approaches. Most projects for public organizations have
   adopted waterfall model in software development lifecycle, however,
   various projects have recently tried to apply an iterative model to
   minimize risks and to enhance quality of software. But empirical results
   of software-intensive development based on the RUP are not well known.
   Therefore, this paper presents process, period, effort and quality
   factors for a software-intensive system development through the study on
