Abstract = {The Rational Unified Process (RUP) is a comprehensive software
   development process framework emphasizing use-cases, architecture focus
   and an iterative approach. RUP is widely known and many organizations
   have tried PF to adopt it. Being a framework, RUP has to, in some way,
   be tailored to the specific context of use, no software development
   project is alike. This paper presents a case study of a Norwegian SME
   that tried to adopt RUP in the simplest way, by introducing the
   methodology by providing comprehensive documentation and some simple
   training. Our study shows that the use of RUP had some positive effects
   but also that the use has been scattered. Interviews with users of RUP
   show that there is a great need of better training and practical support
   in getting most value out of RUP. The key message is that if you
