   simulation and modeling, terrain-obstacle sensing, and perception,
   computing, communication, navigation, mission package selection and
   safety/field exercise support was organized, initial data collection and
   evaluation of early sensor/algorithm candidates for obstacle detection
   were completed and an overall system control architecture (4D-RCS)
   consistent with multivehicle maneuver and intelligent behaviors was
   developed. Demo III's technology integration contract for four
   Experimental Unmanned Vehicles was competitively awarded in January 98.
   The integration effort will provide the infrastructure required to have
   troops interact with the technologies through three successive
   development/experimentation cycles. The second year of the program will
   see field evaluations of subsystem technologies, completion of
   preliminary and critical design reviews, and an initial troop field
